<p class="definition" data-word = 'Traveling vs. Oscillating'>
    Linear motion is <emph>traveling</emph>: you go somewhere. We represent traveling motion with and arrow.
    <br>
    Harmonic motion is <emph>oscillating</emph>: you move and return to your original spot. We represent oscillating motion with a double-sided arrow.
</p>


